CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F428A1776355855
OL,3,CBaby found under floorboards could
OL,4,Chave lived 300 years ago, inquest told
OL,6,FAnother type of radio-carbon dating
OL,7,Findicated a range of possible dates
OL,8,Fthat the baby lived as between 1726
OL,9,Fand 1812.
OL,11,FThe remains were wrapped in a
OL,12,Fnewspaper called The Umpire which was
OL,13,Fdated June 19 1910, the inquest was
OL,14,Ftold.
OL,16,FA forensic anthropologist assisted
OL,17,Fwith the inquiries and it was believed
OL,18,Fthe skeleton was that of a full-term
OL,19,Fbaby of about 40 weeks development.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/5
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
